
Basic guide for beginners: https://product.hubspot.com/blog/git-and-github-tutorial-for-beginners

How to begin a repository:

 Create a local repository: Create a folder in your computer and run git init therein

 Link your local repository to a remote repository in Github.com: git remote add origin https://github.com/[your_repo].git


How to add a file or folder from the local to the remote repository:
 
 Add the file: Every file in the folder containing the local repository can be added to the local repository by git add [file]

 Create a commit: git commit -m "Your message about the commit".

 Change you branch name to match you remote repo name: git branch -m [local branch] [remote branch]  for instance git branch -m master main 
 
 Push to to remote repo: git push -u origin main


Some useful commands:

 See status: git status
 
 See local branches: git branch

